<title>Use gf with CMake</title>
<para>At build time, gf generates a CMake module that is suitable for other projects. Once installed, it is very easy to import gf as a dependency. Here is a simple <computeroutput>CMakeLists.txt</computeroutput> for a projet that uses gf.</para><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">cmake_minimum_required(VERSION<sp/>3.0)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">project(FOOGAME</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/>VERSION<sp/>0.1.0</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">find_package(gf<sp/>REQUIRED)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">add_executable(foogame</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/>foogame.cc</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/>#<sp/>and<sp/>the<sp/>rest<sp/>of<sp/>your<sp/>sources</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">target_link_libraries(foogame</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/>gf::gf0</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para></sect1>
